MQ1 file was not importing correctly because HFC does not translate time greater then 99 seconds into a format that is readable by Aquarius. When it goes into 3 digits ie. (100 seconds) the third digit goes into the space used to dilineate the seperate columns between Count and Time. I modified the file to by deleting the third digits and replacing them with spaces. Every time you see a 20 second count in the discharge details, read it as 120.
